First Lady Melania Trump attended the annual gala at Ford's Theatre as the Honorary Chair. She delivered remarks at the end of the performances, thanking Ford's Theatre and the performers. She also congratulated the recipients of the Lincoln Medal, an award given to individuals who exemplify President Lincoln's legacy. Melania expressed her honor in being part of the evening and emphasized the power of the arts in cultivating the American voice. She thanked Ford's Theatre Society for their dedication to education and leadership in the arts.